The EU changes rules to obtain visa
The people will have to go to the centers on watch for Visa Applicants before their interview in the Consular Section\; the cost will be smaller and as well as the time of delay.
From the 10 of January of 2011 it will change the procedure to transact a visa in the Embassy of the United States and consulates.
With the new procedure, the majority of the applicants will have to go to the centers on watch for Visa Applicants (ASC, by its abbreviations in English) before their interview in the Consular Section.
The personnel of the ASC will take the biometric information from the applicant, who will be reviewed by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will have certain advantages for the aspirings, between whom they are:
The total cost to transact the visa will be smaller, no longer will be necessary to realize a payment to arrange the appointment, another payment to process the request of visa and another one more so that the service of mail gives the document.
The aspiring will only realize a unique payment that will cover the three services.
The present tariff will remain without change: the equivalent to 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for cases of visas with request (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for visas of retailers and investors.
The people who wish to renew their visa will not have to go to an interview with the Consular Official, but they will only go to the nearest ASC where they will present its documents and they will take its tracks them.
Because the biometric information will be taken in the ASC, the applicants who require one second appointment to be interviewed in the Consular Section, will remain in this one less time than in the past.
Also, who ask for visa in the Consulates in Juárez City, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo no longer will pay the extra tariff on watch of 26 dollars.
